!PADS-POWERPCB-V9.5-BASIC! DESIGN DATABASE ASCII FILE 1.0

*PCB*        GENERAL PARAMETERS OF THE PCB

UNITS        1
MAXIMUMLAYER 2
ORIGIN       0.0 0.0

*REMARK* Synthetic test for in-circuit test point import (issue 23637).
*REMARK* TP_BOTTOM_SMD: drill=0, pad on routing layer (layer 0) + soldermask bottom (28)
*REMARK*   -> should import as SMD footprint on B.Cu with correct pad size
*REMARK* TP_TOP_SMD: drill=0, pad on top copper (layer -2) + soldermask top (25)
*REMARK*   -> should import as SMD footprint on F.Cu with correct pad size
*REMARK* The test point via in *SIGNAL* must NOT also appear as a bare PCB_VIA.

*VIA*  ITEMS

*REMARK* NAME DRILL STACKLINES
*REMARK* LEVEL SIZE SHAPE

TP_BOTTOM_SMD  0 4
-2 0 R
-1 0 R
0  1200000 R
28 1200000 R

TP_TOP_SMD  0 4
-2 1200000 R
-1 0 R
0  0 R
25 1200000 R

STDVIA  762000 4
-2 1524000 R
-1 1524000 R
0  1524000 R
0  1524000 R

*PARTDECAL*  ITEMS

RES_0402 M 0 0 0 2 1 0 0
T 0 600000 0 600000 1
T 0 -600000 0 -600000 2
PAD 0 1
-2 600000 R

*PART*       PART ITEMS

R1 RES_0402 0 0 0 0 0

*NET*        NET LIST ITEMS

NET_TP
R1.1 R1.2

*ROUTE*      ROUTING ITEMS

*SIGNAL* NET_TP 0 -2 ;
R1.1                            R1.2
0        0        2 300000 1536
15000000 0        2 300000 1536
15000000 10000000 2 300000 256 TP_BOTTOM_SMD
30000000 10000000 2 300000 1536
30000000 0        2 300000 1536
60000000 0        1 300000 256 TP_TOP_SMD
60000000 0        1 300000 768

*TESTPOINT*

*REMARK* VIA XLOC YLOC SIDE SIGNAME SYMBOLNAME
VIA 15000000 10000000 0 NET_TP TP_BOTTOM_SMD
VIA 60000000 0        1 NET_TP TP_TOP_SMD

*MISC*      MISCELLANEOUS PARAMETERS

LAYER DATA
{
LAYER 1
{
LAYER_NAME Top
LAYER_TYPE ROUTING
}
LAYER 2
{
LAYER_NAME Bottom
LAYER_TYPE ROUTING
}
LAYER 25
{
LAYER_NAME Solder Mask Top
LAYER_TYPE SOLDER_MASK
}
LAYER 28
{
LAYER_NAME Solder Mask Bottom
LAYER_TYPE SOLDER_MASK
}
}

*END*
